Here are both approaches side by side.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView selection changed):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string ID (arrives as string)
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // Approach B — full object (arrives as the original type)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** as `BindingContext` on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- Shell calls ApplyQueryAttributes on the BindingContext automatically -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **Query string** (`?productId=42`) — values arrive as strings; best for simple IDs.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** — values arrive as their original CLR type; best for passing full objects without serialization.
- Shell calls `ApplyQueryAttributes` on the page's `BindingContext` automatically if it implements `IQueryAttributable` — no manual wiring needed.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
